**VERDICT: CASE-C-CORRECT** — no engine line maps PS `SwgVertexConstants` diffuse/emissive to a named slot or a provable `userConstants[N]` / `packedRegisterN` offset.

---

### (a) Rule D — no diffuse/emissive → `userConstants[N]` / `packedRegisterN` table

Rule D only wraps `: register(cN)` → `: packoffset(cN)` and keeps the `cN` token; it does **not** rename symbols or build a semantic map:

```757:767:src/engine/client/application/Direct3d11/src/win32/Direct3d11_HlslRewrite.cpp
	// Input form (vertex_shader_constants.inc):
	//   float4x4  objectWorldCameraProjectionMatrix : register(c0);
	//   ...
	//   ExtendedLightData extendedLightData : register(c60);
	// Output form:
	//   cbuffer SwgVertexConstants : register(b0)
	//   {
	//   float4x4  objectWorldCameraProjectionMatrix : packoffset(c0);
	//   ...
	//   ExtendedLightData extendedLightData : packoffset(c60);
	//   };
```

```959:980:src/engine/client/application/Direct3d11/src/win32/Direct3d11_HlslRewrite.cpp
		// Section bytes with `register` -> `packoffset` substitutions.
		for (std::size_t i = sectionStart; i < sectionEnd; )
		{
			// ...
					std::memcpy(dst + outPos, kPackoffsetToken, kPackoffsetTokenLen);
					// ... `(` + `cN` + `)` verbatim
```

Char-select PS reflection (`packedRegister0..4`, `materialSpecularColor` @ 112, flat `userConstants[17]` @ 128) means the **PS** include declares those names — not that Rule D moved D3D9 `VSCR_material` (c11) into a known `userConstants` index. `materialSpecularColor` @ offset 112 (= `packoffset(c7)`) is the only material-related **named** PS field; that is separate from GAP-2 diffuse/emissive.

The `material[0]/[1]/[2]` chain in `apply()` is explicitly non-evidence (two planner guesses, discovery falsified `material[N]`):

```868:898:src/engine/client/application/Direct3d11/src/win32/Direct3d11_StaticShaderData.cpp
